#: ../../main_window/timeline_view.rst:20
msgid "The Timeline View"
msgstr "La vista Linea temporale"

#: ../../main_window/timeline_view.rst:22
msgid ""
"The Timeline View shows a timescale-adjustable histogram of the numbers of "
"images per **Time Unit** which is selectable by a drop down field. Available "
"graininess of time are **Day**, **Week**, **Month**, and **Year**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../main_window/timeline_view.rst:24
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "The Timeline View shows a timescale-adjustable histogram of the numbers "
#| "of images per time unit which is selectable by a drop down field. To the "
#| "right of that you can choose between a linear or logarithmic histogram. A "
#| "selection frame moves over the histogram. To display the photographs out "
#| "of a certain time frame just click on the corresponding bar. You are not "
#| "restricted to one bar. With :kbd:`Shift+left` click or :kbd:`Ctrl+left` "
#| "click you can add more bars to the first one."
msgid ""
"To the right of that you can choose between a **Linear** or **Logarithmic** "
"histogram using scaling buttons. A selection frame can be moved over the "
"histogram and to display the photographs out of a certain time frame, just "
"click on the corresponding histogram bar. You are not restricted to one bar: "
"with :kbd:`Shift+left` click you can select a range of bars from the "
"histogram, and with :kbd:`Ctrl+left` click you can select more single bars "
"to the first one."
msgstr ""
"La vista Linea temporale mostra un istogramma del numero di immagini per "
"unità di tempo regolabile in base a una scala temporale, che viene "
"selezionata per mezzo di un campo a tendina. Alla destra puoi scegliere tra "
"una scala lineare o logaritmica; una cornice di selezione si muove "
"sull'istogramma. Per visualizzare le fotografie al di fuori di una certa "
"cornice temporale basta fare clic sulla barra corrispondente, ma non sei "
"limitato ad una barra: premendo  :kbd:`Maiusc+sinistro` o :kbd:`Ctrl"
"+sinistro` puoi aggiungere altre barre alla prima."

#: ../../main_window/timeline_view.rst:31
msgid "Timeline Selection Screencast"
msgstr "Registrazione della selezione di una linea temporale"

#: ../../main_window/timeline_view.rst:33
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "In the field right below you can enter a title and save your selection. "
#| "It will then appear in the **Searches** list field below. But the best is "
#| "still to come: the Timeline View offers a search for a search! If you "
#| "have a lot more searches saved than my ridiculous four in the screenshot "
#| "the adaptive search field at the bottom may help to find a certain search."
msgid ""
"In the field right below you can enter a title and save your selection. It "
"will then appear in the **Searches** list field below. But the best is still "
"to come: the Timeline View offers a search for a search. If you have a lot "
"more searches saved in the database, the adaptive search field at the bottom "
"may help to find a certain entry in the list."
msgstr ""
"Nel campo in basso a destra puoi inserire un titolo e salvare la tua "
"selezione: apparirà ora nell'elenco del campo **Ricerche** in basso. Ma il "
"meglio deve ancora venire: la vista Linea temporale offre una ricerca di una "
"ricerca! Se hai molte più ricerche salvate rispetto alle quattro della "
"registrazione mostrata sopra, il campo della ricerca adattiva in basso può "
"aiutarti a trovarne una specifica."

#: ../../main_window/timeline_view.rst:35
msgid ""
"The date-range of the histogram is populated with the time stamp of items "
"registered in the database. For each date matching the histogram bars time-"
"resolution, an item is counted in the statistics. Long bars correspond to "
"dates where a lots of items have been taken in the same graininess-range."
msgstr ""

#: ../../main_window/timeline_view.rst:37
msgid ""
"The icon-view gives the search results of the selection of date. You can "
"select wanted items to post-process contents on batch queue manager or "
"export items to the Internet. From Right sidebar you can filter icon view "
"contents by database properties."
msgstr ""
